{
  "texts": [
    "In the context of mathematics education, these changes aim to address the difficulties experienced by many students in learning mathematics, perceiving the subject as complex in its use of language, spatial reasoning and quantitative skills (Sarma & Ahmed, 2013).",
    "Mathematics education, in particular, is prone to miscommunication between educators and students and traditional methods, such as relying solely on symbolic representations, can hinder students' comprehension (Sarma & Ahmed, 2013).",
    "However, the educational field is not devoid of innovation.",
    "Digital technology has the potential to transform mathematical exploration, making it more diverse and interactive.",
    "When integrated effectively, it has the power to shift the educational paradigm, actively engaging students and granting them agency over their learning experiences (Hoyles, 2018)."
  ]
}